      "reviews": [
        {
          "reviewTitle": "Affordable and Excellent",
          "reviewText": "I got this because I already use the Clean Invisible loose powder and have gotten compliments on it. I figured I\u2019d give the foundation a shot. I was keeping my expectations low but this foundation rules. I deal with dryness and redness and this covers it but literally zero caking, which doesn\u2019t ever happen! It also hit the mark with a color match - Ivory is super balanced. Not too pink or yellow on my skin, and also doesn\u2019t make me look ghostly. It blends in like a tinted moisturizer but still maintains good coverage. Who knew after years of chasing expensive foundations at Sephora I\u2019d find the best experience with Covergirl!",
          "reviewDate": "Reviewed in the United States on December 1, 2025",
          "customer": "Stephanie",
          "customerProfileUrl": "https://www.amazon.com/gp/profile/amzn1.account.AHLEQJAF2L6M2OOCCBJWEJATS4KQ",
          "customerStarsRating": 5,
          "productSpecs": {
            "color": "Ivory",
            "size": "1 Fl Oz (Pack of 1)"
          },
          "helpfulVotes": "32 people found this helpful"
        },
        {
          "reviewTitle": "It is perfect on me",
          "reviewText": "I\u2019m in love with this foundation! The color, \u201cgolden ivory,\u201d is a 100% perfect match on my skin! I\u2019m Italian so I have that olive skin tone. I went to the Covergirl website and used their virtual foundation and shade finder and it picked this shade for me. I highly recommend trying it out, it was so helpful because getting a good color match has always been a problem. I was worried it would look yellow, but it\u2019s so beautiful and glowing that I can\u2019t even tell I\u2019m wearing any foundation at all! I have combo skin with the t-zone oily appearance. When I used it for the first time today I did not use a primer. It covered well for me, it\u2019s thin and lightweight with a natural satin finish. It was not drying at all and I noticed it had a slightly Dewey appearance after i wore it for about an hour. It\u2019s what I was hoping for! At my age now, 62, I\u2019m not looking for that heavy full coverage that usually ends up Cakey looking. Plus I live in Arizona and it\u2019s very hot out and it held up well! This didn\u2019t settle into any of my fine lines, just very natural looking. I hope they never discontinue this, I\u2019m very happy with this product!",
          "reviewDate": "Reviewed in the United States on August 19, 2025",
          "customer": "Lucas Essman",
          "customerProfileUrl": "https://www.amazon.com/gp/profile/amzn1.account.AHPWHDK2PFYZVNXZA3NNK7M2VHAA",
          "customerStarsRating": 5,
          "productSpecs": {
            "color": "Golden Ivory",
            "size": "1 Fl Oz (Pack of 1)"
